HEADWORD: Concentric
<hw>Con*cen"tric</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which has a common center
with something else.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Its pecular relations to its <qex>concentrics</qex>.</q>
